in I of Angoul\u00eame|Alduin I]], Frankish nobleman\n* [[965]] &ndash; [[Arnulf I, Count of Flanders]] (born c. 890)<ref>{{cite book|author1=H. E. L. Mellersh|author2=Neville Williams|title=Chronology of World History|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=PCcOAQAAMAAJ|year=1999|publisher=ABC-CLIO|isbn=978-1-57607-155-7}}</ref>\n* [[973]] &ndash; [[Hermann Billung]], Frankish lieutenant (b. 900)\n*[[1045]] &ndash; [[Ali ibn Ahmad al-Jarjara'i]], Fatimid vizier\n*[[1184]] &ndash; [[George III of Georgia|Giorgi III]], King of Georgia<ref>{{cite book|author=Alexander Mikaberidze|title=Historical Dictionary of Georgia|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=JNNQCgAAQBAJ&pg=PA332|date=6 February 2015|publisher=Rowman & Littlefield Publishers|isbn=978-1-4422-4146-6|pages=332\u2013}}</ref>\n*[[1248]] &ndash; [[Maud Marshal]], English countess (b. 1192)\n*[[1350]] &ndash; [[Alfonso XI of Castile]] (b. 1312)\n*[[1378]] &ndash; [[Pope Gregory XI]] (b. 1336)\n*[[1462]] &ndash; [[Vasily II of Moscow]] (b. 1415)\n*[[1472]] &ndash; [[Janus Pannonius]], Hungarian bishop and poet (b. 1434) \n*[[1482]] &ndash; [[Mary of Burgundy]], Sovereign Duchess regnant of Burgundy, married to [[Maximilian I, Holy Roman Emperor]] (b. 1457)\n*[[1564]] &ndash; [[L\u00fctfi Pasha]], Turkish historian and politician, [[List of Ottoman Grand Viziers|Grand Vizier of the Ottoman Empire]] (b. 1488)\n*[[1572]] &ndash; [[Girolamo Maggi]], Italian polymath (b. c. 1523)\n*[[1598]] &ndash; [[Theodor de Bry]], Belgian-German engraver, goldsmith, and publisher (b. 1528)\n*[[1613]] &ndash; [[Sigismund B\u00e1thory]] (b. 1573)<ref>{{cite book |last=Szab\u00f3 |first=P\u00e9ter K\u00e1roly |editor1-last=Gujd\u00e1r |editor1-first=No\u00e9mi |editor2-last=Szatm\u00e1ry |editor2-first=N\u00f3ra |title=Magyar kir\u00e1lyok nagyk\u00f6nyve: Uralkod\u00f3ink, korm\u00e1nyz\u00f3ink \u00e9s az erd\u00e9lyi fejedelmek \u00e9let\u00e9nek \u00e9s tetteinek k\u00e9pes t\u00f6rt\u00e9nete ''[Encyclopedia of the Kings of Hunga