designer (b. 1900)\n*[[1994]] &ndash; [[Elisabeth Schmid]], German archaeologist and osteologist (b. 1912)<ref>{{cite book |last1=Ogilvie |first1=Marilyn |last2=Harvey |first2=Joy |author-link=Marilyn Bailey Ogilvie| author2-link=Joy Harvey |title=The Biographical Dictionary of Women in Science: Pioneering Lives From Ancient Times to the Mid-20th Century |date=2003 |publisher=Routledge |isbn=978-1-135-96342-2 |page=1716 |url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=FlxsBgAAQBAJ&pg=PT1716#v=onepage&q&f=false |language=en}}</ref>\n*  1994   &ndash; [[Lawrence Wetherby]], American lawyer and politician, 48th [[Governor of Kentucky]] (b. 1908)\n*[[1995]] &ndash; [[Ren\u00e9 Allio]], French director and screenwriter (b. 1924)\n*[[1997]] &ndash; [[Lane Dwinell]], American businessman and politician, 69th [[Governor of New Hampshire]] (b. 1906)\n*  1997   &ndash; [[Ella Maillart]], Swiss skier, sailor, field hockey player, and photographer (b. 1903)\n*[[1998]] &ndash; [[David McClelland]], American psychologist and academic (b. 1917)\n*[[1999]] &ndash; [[Michael Aris]], Cuban-English author and academic (b. 1946)\n*[[2000]] &ndash; [[George Allen (ice hockey)|George Allen]], Canadian ice hockey player and coach (b. 1914)\n*  2000   &ndash; [[Ian Dury]], English singer-songwriter and actor (b. 1942)\n*[[2002]] &ndash; [[Milton Berle]], American comedian and actor (b. 1908)\n*  2002   &ndash; [[Dudley Moore]], English actor (b. 1935)\n*  2002   &ndash; [[Billy Wilder]], Austrian-born American director, producer, and screenwriter (b. 1906)\n*[[2003]] &ndash; [[Edwin Carr (composer)|Edwin Carr]], New Zealand composer and educator (b. 1926)\n*[[2004]] &ndash; [[Robert Merle]], French author (b. 1909)\n*[[2005]] &ndash; [[Wilfred Gordon Bigelow]], Canadian soldier and surgeon (b. 1913)\n*[[2006]] &ndash; [[Dan Curtis]], American director and producer (b. 1928)\n*  2006   &ndash; [[Stanis\u0142aw Lem]], Ukrainian-Polish author (b. 1921)\n*  2006   &ndash; [[Rudolf Vrba]], Czech [[Holo