dash; [[V\u00e4in\u00f6 Siikaniemi]], Finnish javelin thrower, poet, and translator (d. 1932)\n*[[1888]] &ndash; [[George Alfred Lawrence Hearne]], English-South African cricketer (d. 1978)\n*[[1889]] &ndash; [[Yakup Kadri Karaosmano\u011flu]], Egyptian-Turkish journalist, author, and politician (d. 1974)\n*  1889   &ndash; [[Leonard Mociulschi]], Romanian general (d. 1979)\n*[[1890]] &ndash; [[Harald Julin]], Swedish swimmer and water polo player (d. 1967)\n*  1890   &ndash; [[Frederick Dalrymple-Hamilton]], Scottish admiral (d. 1974)\n*[[1891]] &ndash; [[Lajos Zilahy]], Hungarian novelist and playwright (d. 1974)\n*  1891   &ndash; [[Klawdziy Duzh-Dushewski]], Belarusian-Lithuanian architect, journalist, and diplomat, created the [[Flag of Belarus]] (d. 1959)\n*[[1892]] &ndash; [[Ferde Grof\u00e9]], American pianist and composer (d. 1972)\n*  1892   &ndash; [[Thorne Smith]], American author (d. 1934)\n*[[1893]] &ndash; [[Karl Mannheim]], Hungarian-English sociologist and academic (d. 1947)\n*  1893   &ndash; [[G. Lloyd Spencer]], American lieutenant and politician (d. 1981)\n*  1893   &ndash; [[George Beranger]], Australian-American actor and director (d. 1973)\n*[[1894]] &ndash; [[Ren\u00e9 Fonck]], French colonel and pilot (d. 1953)\n*[[1895]] &ndash; [[Roland Leighton]], English soldier and poet (d. 1915)\n*[[1897]] &ndash; [[Douglas Hartree]], English mathematician and physicist (d. 1958)\n*  1897   &ndash; [[Fred Keating]], American magician, stage and film actor (d. 1961)\n*[[1899]] &ndash; [[Francis Ponge]], French poet and author (d. 1988)\n*  1899   &ndash; [[Herbert Arthur Stuart]], German-Swiss physicist and academic (d. 1974)\n*  1899   &ndash; [[Gloria Swanson]], American actress and producer (d. 1983)\n*[[1901]] &ndash; [[Carl Barks]], American illustrator and screenwriter (d. 2000)\n*  1901   &ndash; [[Erich Ollenhauer]], German politician (d. 1963)\n*  1901   &ndash; [[Eisaku Sat\u014d]], Japanese politician, 61st [[Prime Minister of Japan]], [[Nobel Peace Prize|Nobel Prize]] laureate (d. 1975)\n*  1901   &ndash; [[Kenneth Slessor]], Australian journalist and poet (d. 1971)\n*[[1902]] &ndash; [[Sidney Buchman]], American screenwriter and producer (d. 1975)\n*  1902   &ndash; [[Charles Lang]], American cinematographer (d. 1998)\n*[[1903]] &ndash; [[Xavier Villaurrutia]], Mexican poet and playwright (d. 1950)\n*[[1905]] &ndash; [[Leroy Carr]], American singer-songwriter and pianist (d. 1935)\n*  1905   &ndash; [[Rudolf Christoph Freiherr von Gersdorff]], German general (d. 1980)\n*  1905   &ndash; [[Elsie MacGill]], Canadian-American author and engineer (d. 1980)\n*[[1906]] &ndash; [[Pee Wee Russell]], American clarinet player, saxophonist, and composer (d. 1969)\n*[[1909]] &ndash; [[Golo Mann]], German historian and author (d. 1994)\n*  1909   &ndash; [[Ben Webster]], American saxophonist (d. 1973)\n*  1909   &ndash; [[Valery Marakou]], Belarusian poet and translator (d. 1937)\n*[[1910]] &ndash; [[Ai Qing]], Chinese poet and author (d. 1996)\n*[[1911]] &ndash; [[Veronika Tushnova]], Russian poet and physician (d. 1965)\n*[[1912]] &ndash; [[James Callaghan]], English lieutenant and politician, [[Prime Minister of the United Kingdom]] (d. 2005)\n*[[1913]] &ndash; [[Theodor Dannecker]], German [[SS]] officer (d. 1945)\n*[[1914]] &ndash; [[Richard Denning]], American actor (d. 1998)\n*  1914   &ndash; [[Budd Schulberg]], American author, screenwriter, and producer (d. 2009)\n*[[1915]] &ndash; [[Robert Lockwood, Jr.]], American guitarist (d. 2006)\n*[[1917]] &ndash; [[Cyrus Vance]], American lawyer and politician, 57th [[United States Secretary of State]] (d. 2002)\n*[[1920]] &ndash; [[Colin Rowe]], English-American architect, theorist and academic (d. 1999)\n*[[1921]] &ndash; [[Phil Chess]], Czech-American record producer, co-founded [[Chess Records]] (d. 2016)\n*  1921   &ndash; [[Moacir Barbosa Nascimento]], Brazilian footballer and coach (d. 2000)\n*  1921   &ndash; [[Harold Nicholas]], American actor and dance