nd jumper (b. 1881)\n*[[1921]] &ndash; [[Harry Barron]], English general and politician, 16th [[Governor of Western Australia]] (b. 1847)\n*[[1922]] &ndash; [[Nikolay Sokolov (composer)|Nikolay Sokolov]], Russian composer and educator (b. 1859)\n*[[1923]] &ndash; [[James Dewar]], Scottish chemist and physicist (b. 1842)\n*[[1925]] &ndash; [[Carl Neumann]], German mathematician and academic (b. 1832)\n*[[1926]] &ndash; [[Kick Kelly]], American baseball player, manager, and umpire (b. 1856)\n*  1926   &ndash; [[Georges V\u00e9zina]], Canadian ice hockey player (b. 1887)\n*[[1927]] &ndash; [[Joe Start]], American baseball player and manager (b. 1842)\n*  1927   &ndash; [[Klaus Berntsen]], Danish politician, [[Prime Minister of Denmark]] (b. 1844)\n*[[1928]] &ndash; [[Leslie Stuart]], English organist and composer (b. 1863)\n*[[1931]] &ndash; [[Arnold Bennett]], English author and playwright (b. 1867)\n*[[1934]] &ndash; [[Francis William Reitz]], South African lawyer and politician, 5th [[State President of the Orange Free State]] (b. 1844)\n*[[1938]] &ndash; [[William Stern (psychologist)|William Stern]], German-American psychologist and philosopher (b. 1871)\n*[[1940]] &ndash; [[Michael Joseph Savage]], Australian-New Zealand politician, 23rd [[Prime Minister of New Zealand]] (b. 1872)\n*[[1942]] &ndash; [[Julio Gonz\u00e1lez (sculptor)|Julio Gonz\u00e1lez]], Catalan sculptor and painter (b. 1876)\n*[[1943]] &ndash; [[George Monckton-Arundell, 8th Viscount Galway]], English politician, 5th [[Governor-General of New Zealand]] (b. 1882)\n*[[1945]] &ndash; [[Vincent Hugo Bendix]], American engineer and businessman, founded [[Bendix Corporation]] (b. 1881)\n*  1945   &ndash; [[Halid Ziya U\u015fakl\u0131gil]], Turkish author, poet, and playwright (b. 1866)\n*[[1946]] &ndash; [[Karl Groos]], German psychologist and philosopher (b. 1861)\n*[[1949]] &ndash; [[Elisheva Bikhovski]], Israeli-Russian poet (b. 1888)\n*[[1952]] &ndash; [[Kiichiro Toyoda]], Japanese businessman, fo